</LIST>
<LIST>
<HEAD>8. Argument. HONOVR.</HEAD>
<ITEM><HI>HOnour</HI> is <HI>painted,</HI> when it is not with vertue
<HI>poudred;</HI><NOTE PLACE="marg">Honour is vertues Harbour.</NOTE> No cloath takes such deepe tin|cture,
