Liuia</HI> and <HI>Iulia, Augustus</HI> his daughters,
were sisters, but of different natures. Some there
are, who euen from their infancy haue such excel|lent
seeds of natiue goodnesse sowne in them, as
their <HI>dispositions</HI> cannot rellish ought that is irregu|lar.
In arguments of discourse, they are moderate;
in Company temperate; in their resolues constant;
in their desires continent; in their whole course or
