<PB N="212" REF="130">
like our<NOTE N="*" PLACE="marg">These are described to life in the person of an hu<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">orous fantarticke in this pleasant Epig<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">am.</NOTE> <HI>humorous Laie<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">s,</HI> they can affect <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">ought
that others loue, nor rellish ought that others like.
The byas of their fancy runnes still on the fashion;
