It were hard to winne <HI>these</HI> to the loue
of <HI>vertue,</HI> or <HI>those</HI> to delight in <HI>vice.</HI> This might ea|<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters">ly
be illustrated by diuers memorable instances,<NOTE N="*" PLACE="marg">Sic <GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 word"> must eat her break fastis her bed, And is til noon in trimming of her head, and s<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters">s at ta|ble like a mai|den-Bride, And takes all day of nothing but of pride, <Q>God may dae mu<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="2 letters"> in mer|cy to saue her, But what a c<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter">se is he in tha<GAP DESC="illegible" RESP="tech" EXTENT="1 letter"> shall haue her?</Q></NOTE>
personated in such; who from their very Cradle, be|came
